"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test code for macro invocations**\\n\\nI might need to mention the test code for compiling macro invocations in Scala 2. It’s important to ensure that both `scala-reflect` and `pekko-actor` are on the test classpath, although it seems they are already deterministic. I don't want to restate what I've said before, but highlighting these dependencies could help clarify the testing process. Keeping everything aligned will make the testing efforts smoother!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"The 2.0.0-M1 artifact is a small Scala macro/helper artifact whose useful classes depend on provided-scope Pekko Actor and Scala Reflect APIs that are not pulled transitively by a normal test scaffold.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"pekko-parsing_2.13:2.0.0-M1 declares pekko-actor_2.13 as a provided dependency, and LogHelper exposes org.apache.pekko.event.LoggingAdapter from that artifact.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.scala-lang:scala-reflect:2.13.18\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"pekko-parsing_2.13:2.0.0-M1 declares scala-reflect as a provided dependency, and LogHelperMacro uses scala.reflect.macros.blackbox.Context and related macro reflection APIs.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property appears required. For 2.0.0-M1, do not reuse the old org.apache.pekko.http.ccompat pre213/since213 coverage from 1.3.0: those classes are absent from the resolved 2.0.0-M1 jar. Focus coverage on the remaining org.apache.pekko.macros.LogHelper and LogHelperMacro classes; direct Scala source use may need tests placed under an org.apache.pekko package because these APIs are internal/private[pekko].\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The artifact exposes only internal macro/logging helper APIs in 2.0.0-M1, so meaningful coverage may need reflection or package-local Scala tests rather than ordinary public API usage.\",\n    \"Using stale 1.3.0-era provided dependency versions may compile in some cases but does not match the 2.0.0-M1 POM and can hide version-specific failures.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0b3376c9a215b0e4016a430def22d88193bb098cad20f03737\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1088, "output": 2024, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 32808, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782779352852, "responseId": "resp_0b3376c9a215b0e4016a430dd97f888193bb58bd6d3da792b5"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Scala dependencies**\n\nI'm considering if Pekko 2.0 may work with Java 17 and wondering if using version 1.1.5 with LogHelper is still valid. I should check if `scala-reflect` 2.13.17 with `scala-library` 2.13.18 is okay — better yet to use 2.13.18. \n\nI’m curious about what constitutes a \"normal generated test scaffold\" for a Scala library. It seems the existing scaffold already comes with `scala-reflect` and `pekko-actor`. Also, I need to be cautious about potential risks, as the APIs may be intended for internal use only.\n\n**Analyzing test class access**\n\nI can define a test class in the package `org.apache.pekko` to gain access. However, the generated package `org_apache_pekko...` can't extend `private[pekko]`. This could make achieving meaningful coverage challenging since we're dealing only with internal APIs, although reflection might still work.\n\nI’m considering if tests should go under `package org.apache.pekko.macros`. Also, the generated test package is typically sanitized, but there's still an editing option. I need to be cautious about risks, particularly regarding reliance on internal APIs.\n\n**Considering test code for macro invocations**\n\nI might need to mention the test code for compiling macro invocations in Scala 2. It’s important to ensure that both `scala-reflect` and `pekko-actor` are on the test classpath, although it seems they are already deterministic. I don't want to restate what I've said before, but highlighting these dependencies could help clarify the testing process. Keeping everything aligned will make the testing efforts smoother!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0b3376c9a215b0e4016a430dda1814819386bddb38d2c1d9c5\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQw3v8p95lxbuTGQ6gjC3v5s-VWnESWAst21IVz2nY1YRVvaGBngXHh20xA928Z31yGl6vJDZKv1mhoK5QGyKkOON3wTtENmH-fMpjBAuoM2vWIBIcEFC